  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We are talking about now probably somewhere around August of that year when I was freed in April.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was already August, September, when we found out that mother is alive.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we started to correspond.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I can tell you the gladness and then the hope.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I have to emphasize that I felt from then on that I am somewhat of an absolutely fortunate individual, because we had only me and my parents, and all three of us survived in a different location.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And hardly anybody in our own family is intact like the three of us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I started to list people, like my uncle who lived in that town [NON-ENGLISH], and his wife and his daughter-- Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I mentioned maybe a doctor, not necessarily while you are taping this witness testimony, but maybe in our conversation before, that there was a doctor in [NON-ENGLISH] who was my grandmother's brother, who was a physician who practiced medicine in the United States.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And because of marital difficulties, he returned to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he was taken to the concentration camp at his age of well in his 70s.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So was his wife, who taught me while on summer vacation at age 6 and 7 to read Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She was a Hebrew teacher.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And-- and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] both sides of the family and the extended family-- second cousins, uncles-- they were very, very much affected.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was hardly any family who was intact like the three of us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I can't tell you that-- what a-- what a feeling it is to be alive and-- and-- and-- and building a new family, my own, which I am so proud and so happy with.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
